From: kenzok8 <kenzok8@noreply>
Date: 2026-06-29
Subject: [PATCH] daed: use bounded probes for manual latency tests

The dashboard "test all nodes" action waits for the GraphQL mutation to finish.
The old path used ProbeLatency(), which runs the normal health-check path:
10s timeout, up to two attempts, for both TCP4 and TCP6. With many dead or slow
nodes this keeps the dashboard button spinning for a long time.

Use ProbeLatencyFast() for manual dashboard tests. It already exists upstream,
has a 1.5s per-family timeout, and does not mutate the background health state.

Reported: https://github.com/kenzok8/openwrt-daede/issues/20
---
--- a/graphql/service/node/latency_mutation_utils.go
+++ b/graphql/service/node/latency_mutation_utils.go
@@ -108,7 +108,7 @@ func testSingleNodeLatency(option *diale
 	}
 	defer d.Close()
 
-	result, err := d.ProbeLatency()
+	result, err := d.ProbeLatencyFast()
 	if err != nil {
 		msg := err.Error()
 		resolver.MessageV = &msg
